# Local dev: copy to .env, paste keys, restart `npm run dev`
# Netlify production: use SERVER keys (no VITE_ prefix) — keys stay off the public bundle
#
# ─── Local dev (direct client calls) ───
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_google_ai_studio_api_key_here
VITE_ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=your_elevenlabs_api_key_here
VITE_ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=your_elevenlabs_voice_id_here
#
# ─── Netlify server-only (proxy — not visible in F12) ───
# GEMINI_API_KEY=same_as_above
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=same_as_above
# ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=same_as_above
#
# Get a free key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# If Gemini works on localhost but not on Netlify, open the key in Google AI Studio
# and remove HTTP referrer restrictions OR allow https://*.netlify.app/*
#
# Supabase ledger (session memory + dashboard) — public anon key is OK in frontend
# Dashboard: https://yoursite.netlify.app/dashboard
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_or_publishable_key_here
